<item>
            <title>[SPARK-11020] HistoryServer fails to come up if HDFS takes too long to come out of safe mode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-11020</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When HDFS is starting up, it starts in safe mode until the NN is able to read the whole fs image and initialize everything. For a really large NN that can take a while.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the HS is started at the same time, it may give up trying to check whether the event log directory exists, and exit. That&apos;s a little sub-optimal; the HS could wait until HDFS came out of safe mode instead.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
